<subSubSection id="C36879D0FFD3AF2AC9DE9A79FB4F94F6" pageId="6" pageNumber="569" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD3AF2AC9DE9A79FADC943E" blockId="6.[151,1436,259,574]" box="[199,1393,295,322]" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD3AF2AC9DE9A79FEE3943E" bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species is named after Mr. Yu-He Gao, who kindly donated many fossils for our research.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD3AF2AC9DE9A15FB4F94F6" blockId="6.[151,1436,259,574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD3AF2AC9DE9A15FE62941A" bold="true" box="[199,463,331,357]" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Locality and horizon.</emphasis>
Amber mine located near Noije Bum Village, Tanai Township, Myitkyina District, 
<collectingRegion id="49B6E4B9FFD3AF2AC98E9A31FE8794F6" box="[151,298,367,393]" country="Myanmar" name="Kachin" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Kachin State</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3656ACBFFD3AF2AC82C9A2EFE0B94F5" box="[309,422,368,394]" name="Myanmar" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
; unnamed horizon, mid-Cretaceous, Upper Albian to Lower Cenomanian.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36879D0FFD3AF2AC9DE9ACDFB9D9741" pageId="6" pageNumber="569" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD3AF2AC9DE9ACDFB9D9741" blockId="6.[151,1436,259,574]" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD3AF2AC9DE9ACDFEEF94D2" bold="true" box="[199,322,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Lateral sides of clypeus subparallel in anterior half (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD3AF2ACA889ACDFC4694D1" box="[913,1003,403,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
). Left mandible with three apical teeth and two narrowly separated and basally strongly jointed teeth on incisor edge (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD3AF2ACD349AE9FB2794AD" box="[1069,1162,439,466]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
). Penultimate maxillary palpomere about as long as apical one (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD3AF2ACB4D9A85FD03948A" box="[596,686,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Jugal processes asymmetrical, comparatively short; right process longer than left one; inner sides with a tooth (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD3AF2ACB889AA1FD469766" box="[657,747,511,537]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
). Median groove of pronotum weakly developed, shorter than half length of pronotum (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD3AF2AC8A8997DFE5B9741" box="[433,502,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,260,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,595,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-158@6.[151,1436,595,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. General habitus of Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under incident light. A, Dorsal view. B, Ventral view. Scale bars: 1.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457416/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Anterior angles of pronotum not pointed (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD3AF2ACAC7997DFB8F9741" box="[990,1058,547,574]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="6.[151,260,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,595,1883]" captionTargetId="figure-158@6.[151,1436,595,1883]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 5. General habitus of Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under incident light. A, Dorsal view. B, Ventral view. Scale bars: 1.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457416" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457416/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="569">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
