<subSubSection id="C36879D0FFD2AF25C9DE9C2EFE619766" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="572" pageId="7" pageNumber="570" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD2AF2BC9DE9C2EFA2D92F3" blockId="7.[151,1436,1904,2039]" box="[199,1408,1904,1932]" pageId="7" pageNumber="570">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFD2AF2BC9DE9C2EFEF492F5" bold="true" box="[199,345,1904,1930]" pageId="7" pageNumber="570">Description.</emphasis>
Body elongate and flattened, about 
<quantity id="4C8A87BEFFD2AF2BCBF79C2FFCE992F4" box="[750,836,1905,1931]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="7" pageNumber="570" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
long, 1.0 mm wide (maximum width across head).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFD2AF24C9DE9CCBFE8F94AE" blockId="7.[151,1436,1904,2039]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1437,151,465]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="571" pageId="7" pageNumber="570">
Head prognathous, constricted posteriorly, with distinct neck region. Temples (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD2AF2BCD4F9CCBFB0292D0" box="[1110,1199,1941,1967]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="570">Fig. 7B</figureCitation>
) distinctly projected posterolaterally. Eyes small, round and finely facetted, without interfacetal setae. Antennal insertions slightly concealed from above; subantennal grooves absent. Frontoclypeal suture not clearly discerned. Clypeus (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFD2AF2BCC1D9C83FAF19288" box="[1284,1372,2013,2039]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="570">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
) with lateral sides subparallel (or weakly diverging) in anterior portion; anterior margin truncate. Labrum (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDDAF24CC1E9BC9FACD95CE" box="[1287,1376,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
) narrowed anteriorly, apically truncate, with numerous elongate setae. Antennae 11-segmented, moniliform, with weak, 3-segmented club. Mandibles (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDDAF24C8EA9B81FDE19586" box="[499,588,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">Fig. 7H</figureCitation>
) tridentate apically; left mandible with two narrowly separated and basally strongly jointed teeth on incisor edge; right mandible with one blunt tooth on incisor edge. Maxillary palps (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDDAF24CC279A5DFA399462" box="[1342,1428,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
) probably 4-segmented; palpomere 1 short; palpomere 2 elongate; palpomere 3 longer than wide, distinctly longer than half length of apical one. Labial palps 3-segmented; palpomere 1 short; palpomeres 2 and 3 elongate. Ligula (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDDAF24C9B99A31FF5494F6" box="[160,249,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
) biemarginate apically. 
<collectingRegion id="49B6E4B9FFDDAF24CB119A31FDCA94F6" box="[520,615,367,393]" country="Myanmar" name="Chin" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">Mentum</collectingRegion>
strongly transverse. Jugal processes (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDDAF24CD0A9A31FBC194F6" box="[1043,1132,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">Fig. 7A</figureCitation>
) asymmetrical; inner sides with a tooth; right process longer than left one, strongly constricted above tooth; left process weakly constricted above tooth.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF0D7AD3FFDDAF24C98E9DA0FED8928E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="571" startId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" targetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFDDAF24C98E9DA0FED8928E" blockId="8.[151,1436,1790,2033]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24C98E9DA0FE8D9267" bold="true" box="[151,288,1790,1816]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">FIGURE 7.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7251D8FFDDAF24C83E9DA1FDC59267" authority="Li &amp; Cai" authorityName="Li &amp; Cai" authorityYear="2022" box="[295,616,1790,1816]" class="Insecta" family="Prostomidae" genus="Vetuprostomis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="571" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gaoi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24C83E9DA1FE539267" box="[295,510,1791,1816]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">Vetuprostomis gaoi</emphasis>
Li &amp; Cai
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24CB769DA0FD659267" bold="true" box="[623,712,1790,1816]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2354B32FFDDAF24CB769DA0FD659267" box="[623,712,1790,1816]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24CC3F9DA0FA979267" bold="true" box="[1318,1338,1790,1816]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">A</emphasis>
, Mouthparts, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24C86E9C7CFE279243" bold="true" box="[375,394,1826,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">B</emphasis>
, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24CAAE9C7CFC669243" bold="true" box="[951,971,1826,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">C</emphasis>
, Prothorax, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24CDEB9C7CFAAB9243" bold="true" box="[1266,1286,1826,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">D</emphasis>
, Fore leg. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24CC9A9C7CFA3B9243" bold="true" box="[1411,1430,1826,1852]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">E</emphasis>
, Mesothorax, dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24C8A09C18FE67921F" bold="true" box="[441,458,1862,1888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">F</emphasis>
, Hind leg. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24CB5E9C18FDF0921F" bold="true" box="[583,605,1862,1888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">G</emphasis>
, Abdomen, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24CA659C18FC22921F" bold="true" box="[892,911,1862,1888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">E</emphasis>
, Mouthparts, dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="B906F649FFDDAF24CDA09C18FB67921F" bold="true" box="[1209,1226,1862,1888]" pageId="8" pageNumber="571">F</emphasis>
, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFDCAF25C9DE9BC9FB27941A" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">
Pronotal disc longer than wide; anterior angles not pointed; lateral sides subparallel; median groove not clearly discerned. Prosternal process (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDCAF25C8F39BE5FDED95AA" box="[490,576,187,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
) wide, expanding beyond procoxae and meeting broad postcoxal projections, apically truncate. Procoxal cavities (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDCAF25CB219B81FD3C9586" box="[568,657,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
) circular, widely separated. Elytra about 2.6 times as long as width combined; surface with longitudinal carinae. Mesoventrite (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDCAF25CA369A5DFC299462" box="[815,900,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
) relatively narrow. Mesocoxal cavities (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDCAF25CC599A5DFA389462" box="[1344,1429,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">Fig. 7E</figureCitation>
) moderately separated. Exposed portion of metanepisternum elongate and narrow. Metaventral discrimen (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDCAF25CC599A79FA39943E" box="[1344,1428,295,321]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">Fig. 7F</figureCitation>
) short, only visible near the posterior end. Metacoxae (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDCAF25CBEA9A15FCEB941A" box="[755,838,331,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">Fig. 7F</figureCitation>
) not meeting elytra laterally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFDCAF25C9DE9A31FD9A94AE" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">
Legs (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDCAF25C8159A31FED494F6" box="[268,377,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">Fig. 7D,F</figureCitation>
) short. Femora distally with groove on inner side. Tibiae shorter than femora, widened apically with spinose outer apical angle; spurs large and stout, paired on all legs. Tarsi 4-4-4; tarsomeres simple, without ventral lobes. Pretarsal claws simple.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD2A5BFFDCAF25C9DE9A85FE619766" blockId="9.[151,1437,151,537]" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">
Abdomen (
<figureCitation id="134936DEFFDCAF25C85D9A85FE31948A" box="[324,412,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="8.[151,260,1790,1816]" captionTargetBox="[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetId="figure-152@8.[161,1427,486,1765]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 7. Vetuprostomis gaoi Li &amp; Cai sp. nov., holotype, NIGP177908, under confocal microscopy. A, Mouthparts, ventral view. B, Temporal projection (arrowhead), ventral view. C, Prothorax, ventral view. D, Fore leg. E, Mesothorax, dorsal view. F, Hind leg. G, Abdomen, ventral view. E, Mouthparts, dorsal view. F, Elytral apex, dorsal view. Abbreviations: cl, clypeus; el, elytron; ey, compound eye; jp, jugular process; lb, labrum; lbp, labial palp; md, mandible; msv, mesoventrite; mt, mentum; mtf, metafemur; mttb, metatibia; mtts, metatarsus; mxp, maxillary palp; pc, procoxa; pf, profemur; ps, prosternum; ptb, protibia; ptc, protrochanter; pts, protarsus; v1–5, ventrites 1–5. Scale bars: 200 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6457422" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6457422/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="572">Fig. 7G</figureCitation>
) with five ventrites. Ratio of ventrite lengths along middle: 2.4: 1.8: 1.4: 1.0: 1.4. Ventrite 5 apically broadly rounded.
</paragraph>
